Package de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.searchAlgorithms.depthFirst.trailelements

Provides classes that represent elements to be added to a depth first execution trail.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
TrailElement A TrailElement is an element that can be added to the trail.
 

Class Summary
ArrayRestore This TrailElement is the counterpiece for the xastore instructions.
FieldPut This TrailElement is the abstract super class for InstanceFieldPut and StaticFielPut.
FrameChange This TrailElement indicates that the current Frame has changed and can be used to set the frame previously executed as the current one.
InstanceFieldPut This TrailElement takes an objectref, a field and an object as its initialization argument.
Pop This TrailElement indicates that the topmost element of the current operand stack has to be popped.
PopFromFrame This TrailElement indicates that the topmost element of the operand stack of the specified frame has to be popped.
Push This TrailElement takes an object as its initialization argument.
Restore This TrailElement is the counterpiece for the xstore and the iinc instructions.
StaticFieldPut This TrailElement takes an static reference to an object (InitializedClass), a field and an object as its initialization argument.
VmPop This TrailElement extends Pop and indicates that the topmost element of the current virtual machine stack has to be popped.
VmPush This TrailElement extends Push and takes an object as its initialization argument.
 

Package de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.searchAlgorithms.depthFirst.trailelements Description

Provides classes that represent elements to be added to a depth first execution trail. They can be used to revert the execution space to a branch of the execution tree visited formerly.
